### Code blocks
#. READ IT because I'm going to use it everywhere!

Code blocks are the best thing in my opinion.
And making one is very very simple, trust me!

We start and end a block with `¬`¬`¬̀`

Such as {{s
	```C++
#include <iostream>

int main(int argc, char** argv) {
	std::cout << "Mark it all with MarkRight!¬:tm:\n";

	return 0;
}
	```
Note that you can add the name of the language you're working with,
which will tell the parser how to lint the code you've wrote!
}}
One more thing, normally we'd use the `\` as an ignore character,
but since it's a very common character in programming I have chosen to replace it
with the `¬¬` character, it's on most extended keyboards, like the US-international, etc.
And comes with a lot more benefit.

