Oops I almost forgot to do what you just saw what I did was I just put a footnote index:

```
My text with some stuff[^a-fancy-footnote] and more handsome text!
```

And your footnote ```
[^a-fancy-footnote]

[^\] ;; this is for the end of the note
```

Footnotes have an interesting behaviour we also put a lot of efforts in,
when your text is separated by big horizontal lines with `---`, the parser grabs all the footnotes
in the section it's currently reading and puts it all at the end. like in this part here, we're at the end,
if there was more they would also be here at the end, in the order they appeared in the document.

If you want certain notes to figure at the end you should use [^^footnote-name]
to redirect at the end.

One more thing, if you wish to have a custom name on your footnote, use the following syntax,
```
Der vogel[^de-vogel:"nm"]

[^de-vogel]
==Der vogel==, *Masculine name*.
1. The bird^name^
[^/]
```
